parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Failure (Fuel Hose/Fuel Pipe Rupture)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to engine fires, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Fuel smell coming from under the hood
fuel leaks
engine check light/airbag light comes on
fuel injection system flooding
vehicle unable to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to properly repair the fuel pressure regulator can lead to fuel system pressure increases, resulting in fuel leaks and potential engine fires.
symptoms: Fuel smell coming from under the hood
fuel leaks
engine check light/airbag light comes on
fuel injection system flooding
vehicle unable to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall parts can lead to delayed or incomplete repairs, leaving the vehicle in an unsafe condition.
symptoms: Dealer unable to obtain parts to correct the defect
dealer informs consumer that parts are not available
consumer experiences repeated delays in getting recall repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Front end alignment issues can cause uneven tire wear, reduced vehicle stability, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle vibrates or shakes while driving
especially at high speeds
front end is out of line
vehicle drifts or pulls to one side
uneven tire wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake system failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Vibrations while braking
premature wear on brake pads
squealing or grinding noises while braking
rear end jerks forward when applying brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Wheel bearing failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle shakes or vibrates while driving
especially at high speeds
strong oil smell
wheel bearing explosion.
